tool.name: QuakeEffectedElderly_CA

param.name: in_workspace
param.dialogReference: The workspace folder where outputs should be saved.

param.name: in_table
param.dialogReference: USGS 30-day earthquake data feed (https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/feed/v1.0/summary/all_month.csv)

param.name: in_feature
param.dialogReference: State census polygon feature class, "State_2010Census_DP1", which is located in the "Profile-County_Tract" geodatabase of the zipped data package. Geodatabase can be found through Tiger data webpage: (https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/tiger-data.html)

param.name: in_feature2
param.dialogReference: County census polygon feature class, "County_2010Census_DP1", which is located in the "Profile-County_Tract" geodatabase of the zipped data package. Geodatabase can be found through Tiger data webpage: (https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/tiger-data.html)

param.name: out_feature3
param.dialogReference:
Total number of earthquakes (USGS, 2019) per California county with relevant census data on the effected elderly populations (US Census, 2010). Output is a polygon feature class. Count of points is located within the attribute table and can be symbolized on the map, or exported to a table.

Suggested output name, "QuakeEffectedElderly_CA_yymmdd". "yymmdd" should correspond to the most recent date of the USGS earthquake dataset.

tool.summary: This tool converts the USGS 30-day earthquake csv file to a point feature class. State and county polygons are filtered down to California only. The quakes that occurred within the 30-day period are summarized within California's county boundary polygons and the total number counted. Fields are altered to deliver a new data table highlighting relevant census data and showing the effected elderly population.
tool.usage: For creating daily data reports on how many earthquakes occurred within California counties and filtering data relevant to the effected elderly population.
